Vice President Kamala Harris spoke at a rally in support of Karen Bass, who is running for mayor of Los Angeles. Harris praised Bass for her dedication to fighting for the people and emphasized the importance of the upcoming election. She reminded the audience of the power of their vote and the impact it has on issues such as child poverty, healthcare, infrastructure, and reproductive rights. Harris also discussed the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion and called for the passage of the Women's Health Protection Act. She highlighted the global implications of the state of democracy in the United States and urged the audience to fight for and protect it.